{"id":37302,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francis_Ford_Coppola","text":"Francis Ford Coppola (born April 7, 1939) is an American director and movie producer. He directed the \"Godfather\" trilogy and the Vietnam War epic \"Apocalypse Now\". He is part of the group called the New Hollywood. This group includes Martin Scorsese, Terrence Malick, Robert Altman, Woody Allen, William Friedkin, Philip Kaufman, and George Lucas. In the 1970s they made movies in a different way.\nCoppola was born in Detroit. At age two, he moved to Woodside, Queens, New York City.\nMany of his relatives are famous. Actor Nicolas Cage is his nephew. Sofia Coppola is his daughter. Roman Coppola is his son. His first child Gian-Carlo Coppola died in 1986.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":48},{"uri":"Movie_director","surface_form":"director","offset":57},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":70},{"uri":"Producer","surface_form":"producer","offset":76},{"uri":"The_Godfather","surface_form":"Godfather","offset":103},{"uri":"Trilogy","surface_form":"trilogy","offset":114},{"uri":"Vietnam_War","surface_form":"Vietnam War","offset":130},{"uri":"Epic_film","surface_form":"epic","offset":142},{"uri":"Apocalypse_Now","surface_form":"Apocalypse Now","offset":148},{"uri":"New_Hollywood","surface_form":"New Hollywood","offset":200},{"uri":"Martin_Scorsese","surface_form":"Martin Scorsese","offset":235},{"uri":"Terrence_Malick","surface_form":"Terrence Malick","offset":252},{"uri":"Robert_Altman","surface_form":"Robert Altman","offset":269},{"uri":"Woody_Allen","surface_form":"Woody Allen","offset":284},{"uri":"William_Friedkin","surface_form":"William Friedkin","offset":297},{"uri":"Philip_Kaufman","surface_form":"Philip Kaufman","offset":315},{"uri":"George_Lucas","surface_form":"George Lucas","offset":335},{"uri":"Detroit","surface_form":"Detroit","offset":419},{"uri":"Woodside%2C_Queens","surface_form":"Woodside, Quee